{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, after investigating the \"why,\" we delve into the \"how,\" and it reveals that according to the users, explanations should be rendered concisely and categorically, and explanations need to include non-technical information.",
    "Additionally, the system should provide a certain amount of control over the recommendations and explanations because they think that if the recommendation is understandable, they can give feedback to the recommender system to rectify the suggestion if necessary.",
    "Users also prefer local explanations rather than global ones.",
    "Global explanations may create cognitive overload, impairing decision-making capability.",
    "Analyzing the latter part of RQ2 (\"how access to explanations will impact users' social media usage\") reveals that based on their initial understanding, users think explainable recommendations will positively influence their social media experience and usage."
  ]
}